node.text:
This is one of the new books I ordered this summer and I am so excited to share it with my students!✨⁣
⁣
As part of the Teach for Justice Campaign, today I am sharing this incredible book along with discussion questions and an activity that you can do with your students!⁣
⁣
This book and activity are just the tip of the iceberg in terms of bringing more discussion around equity and diversity into the classroom. These conversations and your own research around issues of diversity and equity should be continued throughout the entire year!⁣
⁣
Make sure to follow #teachforjusticecampaign for more books and activities!

node.text:
Rearranged some things after school yesterday to make them easier to reach, including my teacher toolbox! ✨⁣
⁣
Now that I have a new teacher toolbox and labels I’m using it a lot more frequently! Which was difficult because it was on a shelf behind my projector screen! So now it has a new location! Still getting used to it so I’m not sure if I’ll keep it here or move it again, but at least it’s easier to reach throughout the day!
⁣
Do you have a teacher toolbox?⁣
⁣
Toolbox labels are in my store! The link is in my profile! ⁣
⁣
Toolbox is linked in my “links” story highlight!💕

node.text:
Our sticker reward chart is a hit again this year! ✨⁣
⁣
Do you use stickers in your classroom? ⁣
⁣
I love asking my students what types of stickers they would like to have and order packs based on their interests!⁣
⁣
This year’s requests included:⁣
✨ Dogs/animals⁣
✨ Candy⁣
✨ Food⁣
✨ Brand logos⁣
✨ Motivational quotes⁣
 and more!⁣
⁣
What stickers are your students loving this year?⁣
⁣
I have a whole blog post about how I use stickers in my classroom here: https://bit.ly/classroomstickers and can find some of my favorite sticker packs here: https://bit.ly/studentstickers 💕

node.text:
Mani Monday inspo + my favorite glue on nail tips below! Also how gorgeous are these ombré glitter nails?!✨⁣
⁣
💗 You can trim or file @redaspenlove nails just like you would your natural nails! I usually do this after putting them on (if needed)!⁣
⁣
💗 If you are in between nail sizes, you can size up and then file the sides of the nail a little for a perfect fit!⁣
⁣
💗 I always keep a tube of nail glue in my purse! That way if a nail pops off I can just glue it right back on! (I got this tip from Hannah @misswestbest!)⁣
⁣
💗 Practice makes perfect! It may take a few times to figure out how much glue to use for your nails and what sizes work best for you, but each time you put them on it should get easier!⁣
⁣
Let me know if these tips were helpful! Wanna try them out? You can shop the nails I use with the link in my profile! 💕

Made it through the first full week of this school year! ✨⁣
⁣
Tell me something good about your week! One of my favorite moments from the week was singing the “Tour the States” song with my class! They are super into it and one of my students even claimed that it was the first non-cringey song that he’s heard in school! 🤣⁣
⁣
Let me know something that made you smile this week in the comments! 💕

node.text:
These positive affirmations are part of our daily morning routine! ✨⁣
⁣
Our morning routine includes:⁣
💗Morning meeting⁣
💗Our school PBIS chant⁣
💗Saying these positive affirmations as a class! ⁣
⁣
It’s my favorite way to start our mornings and I love how much this routine helps with building a positive classroom community!⁣
⁣
What’s your favorite part of your classroom morning routine?⁣
⁣
You can grab the Positive Affirmation Door downloadable file here: https://bit.ly/classdoorbanner I got mine printed at Staples! I included the step by step directions with the download!

node.text:
Throwback to the first day of school! ✨⁣
⁣
I can’t believe we have already been in school for over a week now! It feels so good to be getting all our routines and procedures down, plus I feel like my students are starting to get used to all my singing + super funny jokes 🤪⁣
⁣
Have you started school yet? If so how many days of school have you had??

node.text:
Hands down THE best student whiteboard erasers! ✨⁣
⁣
These felt squares come in a pack of 44 and they are all different colors so it’s easy for students to know which one is theirs! I’ve been using these for the past few years and love them!⁣
⁣
Do you use student whiteboards? (Ours are nothing fancy! They are made of a paper material and come with our math program, but we use them all the time!)⁣
⁣
Affiliate link to the felt squares I use: https://amzn.to/3DiOKXA or you can find it in my “links” story highlight! 💕

node.text:
First week of school outfits! ✨⁣
⁣
Do you have a short week your first week of school or is it a full week?⁣
⁣
I love that our first day back is in the middle of the week! It means we only have a 3 day week and helps everyone ease back into things! This week was all about building our classroom community and establishing routines + procedures and next week we are diving into curriculum (and continuing to build relationships + routines of course)!

Outfit details are linked on liketoknow.it! The link is in my profile! Small shops are tagged in each picture! 💕
